<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a3b6dcc-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s4606"><num value="4606">§ 4606.</num><heading> Protection of information</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a3b6dcd-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s4606/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Freedom of Information Act</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/usc/t5/s552">Section 552 of title 5</ref> shall not apply to information obtained by the Federal Government on a confidential basis under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s4602/b/5">section 4602(b)(5) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a3b6dce-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s4606/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Intellectual property</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other provision of law, intellectual property, trade secrets, and technical data owned and developed by Sematech or any of the participants in Sematech may not be disclosed by any officer or employee of the Department of Defense except as provided in the provision included in the memorandum of understanding pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s4602/b/5">section 4602(b)(5) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a3b6dcf-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/180/dA/tII/s276">Pub. L. 100–180, div. A, title II, § 276</ref>, <date date="1987-12-04">Dec. 4, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1071">101 Stat. 1071</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
